stories.notes:
ALL URLs in this service are wrong — they 404 against the live API. Here are the CORRECT endpoints (verified live June 2026):

1. AGENCIES: GET /references/toptier_agencies/
   Response: { results: [{ agency_name, toptier_code, abbreviation }] }
   Map: name=agency_name, toptierCode=toptier_code, abbreviation=abbreviation

2. GEOGRAPHY: POST /search/spending_by_geography/
   Body: { filters: { time_period: [{ start_date, end_date }] }, geo_layer: 'state', scope: 'recipient_location' }
   Response: { results: [{ shape_code, display_data, aggregated_amount }] }
   FY2024 = start 2024-10-01, end 2025-09-30

3. DISASTER: Same endpoint, add def_codes to filters:
   Body: { filters: { time_period: [...], def_codes: ['L'] }, geo_layer: 'state' }

4. DEF CODES: GET /references/def_codes/
   Response: { results: [{ code, label, group }] }

CRITICAL: fetchWithRetry must support POST with JSON body (currently GET only). fetchAllPages must paginate via POST body { page: N }, not URL query.
Update usa-spending.types.ts raw types to match new response shapes.
Do NOT change return types of service methods — sync.service.ts depends on them.
